    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: NVIM v0.5.0-427-g1f56f9a4b\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently? No, same behavior\r\n- Operating system/version: Arch Linux, latest\r\n- Terminal name/version: kitty, xfce4-terminal, guake\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-kitty, xterm-256color for xfce4-terminal and guake\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n1) Open a new html file (.html extension required)\r\n2) Type random characters until you reach 80 chars.\r\n3) Repeat on a new line.\r\n4) Type V to enter visual linewise mode and highlight the two lines.\r\n5) Type gq\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nThe cursor is a line.\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nThe cursor should be a block.\r\n",
